text.tspan: Flagging Operation on a Single-Lane Circular Intersection
1. Flaggers shall follow the procedures provided in Sections 6D.05 and 6D.06.
When crosswalks or other pedestrian facilities are closed or relocated, temporary facilities (see
Figure 6P-29) shall be detectable and shall include accessibility features consistent with the features
present in the existing pedestrian facility.
At night, fagger stations shall be illuminated, except in emergencies.
4. Flaggers on each approach to the intersection should coordinate with each other so that traffc proceeds
through the circular intersection from only one entry point at any one time.

6. Since the geometrics of the circular intersection will temporarily be altered, consideration should be
given to establishing a truck detour for the duration of the project.
7. For intermediate or long-term work, the circular intersection should be closed if traffc cannot be
accommodated, and traffc detoured with appropriate detour signing (see Figure 6P-8) provided.
